  "description": "Ten-turn debugging session that intentionally accumulates enough repository context, logs, and recall prompts to force baseline compaction before the final recall questions.",
  "worst_case_token_count": 238000,
  "prompt_turns": [
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 0,
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Inspect the failing background sync worker and summarize the top three suspected causes without changing code.",
      "estimated_tokens": 22000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 1,
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The worker likely fails because retry state leaks across jobs, the queue adapter swallows 429s, and the sync cursor is not checkpointed after partial success.",
      "estimated_tokens": 19000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Search the queue package, the retry middleware, and the worker metrics path; collect every place that mentions sync cursor, retry budget, and rate limit backoff.",
      "estimated_tokens": 26000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 3,
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The search surfaced retry budget enforcement in queue-runner.ts, backoff jitter in retry-policy.ts, and cursor persistence in sync-state.ts.",
      "estimated_tokens": 18000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Read the implicated files and explain which state survives retries, which metrics are emitted, and where a partial-success cursor can be lost.",
      "estimated_tokens": 28000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 5,
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "State survives retries in the in-memory retry ledger, metrics emit queue depth and retry attempts, and partial-success cursor loss happens before the final checkpoint write.",
      "estimated_tokens": 19000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Propose a minimal fix and note what evidence we would need later to prove the bug is actually fixed.",
      "estimated_tokens": 22000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 7,
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The minimal fix is to checkpoint the cursor before acknowledging partial success and to preserve rate-limit metadata in retry state; later proof needs a targeted retry regression test and an end-to-end queue replay.",
      "estimated_tokens": 21000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Without rereading files, answer recall questions about the retry ledger, checkpoint location, and the test evidence you recommended.",
      "estimated_tokens": 32000
    },
    {
      "session_id": "debug-session-1",
      "turn_idx": 9,
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The retry ledger is in queue-runner.ts, the checkpoint must move ahead of partial-success acknowledgement in sync-state.ts, and the recommended evidence is a retry regression plus queue replay.",
      "estimated_tokens": 31000
    }
  ],
